                    "$3 \\times 1 = 3$, $3 \\times 2 = 6$, $3 \\times 3 = 9 \\equiv 1$, $3 \\times 4 = 12 \\equiv 4$, $3 \\times 5 = 15 \\equiv 7$, $3 \\times 6 = 18 \\equiv 2$, $3 \\times 7 = 21 \\equiv 5$, $3 \\times 8 = 24 \\equiv 0$.",
